Name: Relief of Punt Expedition from Deir el-Bahari
Description: This relief depicts the travel route of Queen Hatshepsut's expedition to Punt with scenes and texts. This fragment shows some people of Punt carrying sticks. The Punt expedition allowed the Egyptian travelers to exchange their merchandise for the products of Punt, such as incense, myrrh, ivory, ebony, malachite, gold, and electrum.
